  "prompt": "How is money circulated?",
  "response": "Money is circulated through several key mechanisms:\n\n1. Central Bank Operations\n- Printing and distributing physical currency\n- Regulating money supply through monetary policy\n- Controlling interest rates\n\n2. Banking System\n- Banks lend money to individuals and businesses\n- Creating credit through fractional reserve banking\n- Transferring funds between accounts\n\n3. Economic Transactions\n- Spending and earning in daily commerce\n- Wages paid to workers\n- Purchasing goods and services\n- Business-to-business exchanges\n\n4. Government Spending\n- Social welfare payments\n- Government contracts\n- Salaries for public employees\n\n5. Financial Markets\n- Stock trading\n- Investment activities\n- Currency exchanges\n\n6. Electronic Transactions\n- Online banking\n- Credit/debit card payments\n- Digital payment platforms\n\n7. Remittances\n- Money transfers between individuals\n- International money transfers\n\n8. Investment and Savings\n- Circulation through investment vehicles\n- Bank deposits and withdrawals\n\nThese interconnected mechanisms ensure continuous money circulation throughout the economy, enabling economic activity and growth.",
